<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="246" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d246">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">701.1611/188a</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Salvadoran Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leiva</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-13">May 13, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chargé d’affaires</hi>: I was shocked to
                            learn of the injuries which you suffered last night and I hasten to
                            extend to you an expression of my regret. I assure you that the police
                            will make every effort to apprehend the offenders.</p>
                        <p>I trust that you will recover promptly and I want you to know that you
                            have my deepest sympathy.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>